## Basic Docker Syntax

Key commands for managing Docker images:

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `docker pull nginx` | Downloads the latest version of the image titled "nginx". |
| `docker image ls` | Lists all images stored on the local system. |
| `docker image rm <image>` | Removes an image from the local system. |

> Questions in this section are straightforward if you follow along with the reading material.

