## Running Your First Container

Key commands for running and managing containers:

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `docker run -it helloworld /bin/bash` | Runs the container interactively and opens a `/bin/bash` shell for input. |
| `docker run -d <image>` | Runs a container in detached mode (runs in the background). |
| `docker run -p 80:80 <image>` | Binds the container to port 80 on the host machine. |
| `docker ps` | Lists all currently running containers. |
| `docker ps -a` | Lists all containers, including stopped ones. |

